727623f-b.title: Queens: Northern Boulevard - 161st Street
727623f-b.text:
Northern Boulevard, at the N.W. corner of 161st Street (old
21st Street.), showing the W.H. Wilkins house of 1860. It was accuired
by the Hildreth Estate in 1891 with 60.5 acres of land. In 1909 the
Riekirt Finley Realty Company accuired possession and subdivided the
farm into lots. This house, erected in 1832, was still standing in
1934. This is a set of four views. The first two show the east and
south side of the house. Views 3 and 4 show the west and south side.
1924.
View 2: April 1925.
View 3: January 1923.
View 4: March 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
